bug.short_desc: SDDM's default theme/colors are very hard to read
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1277341 Screenshot of the SDDM login screen
Description of problem: It is very hard to see, read anything in the light-grey text on white background theme/color-setup of the SDDM login screen. See attached sddm.png
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): sddm.x86_64 0.14.0-8.fc26 @anaconda sddm-breeze.noarch 5.9.5.1-1.fc26 @updates-testing sddm-kcm.x86_64 5.9.5-1.fc26 @updates-testing
How reproducible: Always.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Reebot. 2. See SDDM (KDE's) login screen.
Actual results: Very hard to read.
Expected results: User friendly, easy to read colors (theme).
Additional info: I chose the sddm component, but it can be sddm-breeze or sddm-kcm. Please reassign it as needed.
Looks like the background image is missing, hardly a sddm issue since you are using a specific theme.
This is a default F26 install from F26 KDE Live iso without any changes (as far as i recall). The only changes came in with updates.

a problem with a recent f26-backgrounds update, https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-dfd1fbf1a4
should be fixed by newer: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-ec3e64c89e
f26-backgrounds-26.2.2-1.fc26 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 26. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-6f9e2042dc

f26-backgrounds-26.2.2-1.fc26 has been pushed to the Fedora 26 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report. See https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/QA:Updates_Testing for instructions on how to install test updates. You can provide feedback for this update here: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-6f9e2042dc

The f26-backgrounds-26.2.2-1.fc26 update fixes the issue. The background image is back.
Thanks!
f26-backgrounds-26.2.2-1.fc26 has been pushed to the Fedora 26 stable repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.
